| Rep tour 26/10/18 |

Instagram: swifts.dragons

summary: My name’s Zoe, and I’m coming to see you Melbourne in less than 20 days! This is my third time seeing you, after RED and 1989,...
body:
Hey Tay!

My name’s Zoe, and I’m coming to see you Melbourne in less than 20 days! This is my third time seeing you, after RED and 1989, and my last time as a teenager as I’ll be 18 next May.

For 10 years I’ve been fighting dragons with you, and I am so thankful for your music and all that you have taught me in this time. You have been there for the most crucial points of my life and my love for you helped me to find the greatest friends I have today.

The 1989 era meant the world to me. 2015 was the year that I started high school, and it was also the year where you released the shake it off music video. I was and still am obsessed with it because you were a ballerina, like me.

In 2016 I was at Disneyland the day you visited, but I was in my hotel room with pneumonia. Even though I know that you didn’t meet anyone that day, I felt as though that I had missed my chance.

After you released LWYMMD I made a fun little tag yourself. It actually got quite popular but I never think you saw it. I don’t mind that you have never noticed me, for I know that it doesn’t make me more or less of a swiftie. My time will come.

I have never been fortunate enough to be in the pit or on the ground or anywhere close to you, but even on level three of a stadium I will always support and love you and dance the night away. So that’s where I’ll be on the Melbourne show with my mum and sister. We might be far away with not the greatest seats, but we will be there with you.

I cannot wait to see you again soon. Love you taylor, forever and always ❤️

@taylorswift @taylornation
